<Folder><name>Start / End</name><Placemark><name>START: Derby</name><styleUrl>#start</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>123.631000,-17.301000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>END: Kununurra</name><styleUrl>#end</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>128.742100,-15.774600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Windjana Gorge turnoff</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>124.938600,-17.432200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tunnel Creek turnoff</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>125.151400,-17.624200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lennard River crossing</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>125.223300,-17.026400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Imintji</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>125.228900,-17.016700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bell Gorge turnoff</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>125.223600,-16.991400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mount Barnett (Manning Gorge)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>125.904700,-16.648600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Galvans Gorge</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>126.185600,-16.488900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Drysdale River Station</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>126.381100,-15.738300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mitchell Falls turnoff (Kalumburu Rd)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>126.716100,-15.758900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Pentecost River crossing</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>127.452800,-15.722800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>El Questro Station</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>127.996700,-16.016700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Windjana Gorge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Devonian limestone gorge — a 350 million-year-old fossil reef from when this country was tropical sea floor. Freshwater crocodiles bask on the sandbanks; safe to walk past at distance.]]></description><Point><coordinates>124.938600,-17.432200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tunnel Creek</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[750 m natural tunnel cut through the same limestone reef. Wade through with a torch; bats roosting overhead. Hideout of Jandamarra, the Bunuba resistance leader killed by police in 1897.]]></description><Point><coordinates>125.151400,-17.624200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bell Gorge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Iconic Kimberley swimming hole — multi-tier waterfall into a cliff-walled pool. 1 km walk in from the parking area. Best around 10am for sun on the water.]]></description><Point><coordinates>125.223600,-16.991400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Manning Gorge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Reached by an ankle-deep creek crossing and a 2.5 km hike. Big swimming pool below a 30 m waterfall. The cattle station here (Mount Barnett, run by the Kupungarri Aboriginal community) sells fuel and supplies.]]></description><Point><coordinates>125.904700,-16.648600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mitchell Falls (Punamii-Uunpuu)</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Four-tier waterfall in remote Mitchell Plateau country — a long detour up the Kalumburu Road, 4WD high-clearance only. Helicopter flights from the airstrip. Sacred site for Wunambal Gaambera people.]]></description><Point><coordinates>126.716100,-15.758900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Pentecost River crossing</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Tidal crossing — saltwater crocodiles are present. Time the crossing for low water; check depth on foot before driving. The Cockburn Range fills the horizon behind you.]]></description><Point><coordinates>127.452800,-15.722800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>El Questro / Emma Gorge</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Million-acre cattle station turned wilderness park. Emma Gorge is a 1.5 km walk to a fern-curtained pool with a thermal warm spring on its eastern wall. Sunrise/sunset chairlifts in the property's gorges.]]></description><Point><coordinates>127.996700,-16.016700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
